Current Player-1 inventory  
- 17 Wheat   → 5 points total  
- 12 Wood    → 10 points total  
- 9  Sheep   → 18 points total  
- 5  Brick   → 20 points total  
- 25 Ore     → 36 points total  

Total value now: 89

Incoming offer: 10 Sheep, 5 Wheat → 5 Ore  

If I accept, what do I gain/lose?  

Lose 5 Ore → –7.2 value/share (5 × 36/25 = 7.2)  

Gain 10 Sheep → +20 (10 each worth 2.0)  
Gain 5 Wheat → +1.47 (5 × 5/17 ≈ 1.47)

Waiting till later seems wasteful—Player 0 keeps proposing different Ore deals, so Ore is clearly the game’s choke-point. I should grab value while it’s handed to me.

Player 0 is offering 10 Sheep (value 20) + 5 Wheat (value ≈1.5) for 5 Ore (value 7.2). Net surplus ≈14.3. This instantly boosts my total value to ~103.3, and puts 5 of my 25 Ore to good use.

Reply:

[Accept]
